{"id":"332561320_A_refined_method_for_computing_bibliographic_coupling_strengths","abstract":"We propose a new method for computing the bibliographic coupling strength between two documents. This new method is based on the TF-IDF formula from the field of information retrieval. It is shown that this formula is a valid alternative for the original formula introduced by Kessler and is, from a probabilistic point of view, a correction of the Vladutz-Cook formula. We further define a cosine based similarity formula generalizing the Sen-Gan coupling angle formula.","authors":["si Shen","Danhao Zhu","Ronald Rousseau","Xinning Su"],"meta":["May 2019Journal of Informetrics 13(2):605-615","DOI:10.1016/j.joi.2019.01.012"],"references":["238123710_Understanding_Inverse_Document_Frequency_On_Theoretical_Arguments_for_IDF","234412386_On_Bibliographic_Networks","220433193_Co-Citation_Analysis_Bibliographic_Coupling_and_Direct_Citation_Which_Citation_Approach_Represents_the_Research_Front_Most_Accurately","37439787_Hierarchical_Cooperation_Achieves_Optimal_Capacity_Scaling_in_Ad_Hoc_Networks","313047208_A_new_methodological_approach_to_bibliographic_coupling_and_its_application_to_research-front_and_other_core_documents","311395129_A_new_bibliographic_coupling_measure_with_descriptive_capability","292406915_A_mathematical_extension_of_the_idea_of_bibliographic_coupling_and_its_applications","286751589_Information_theory_and_the_retrieval_of_recorded_information","260282046_Scholarly_Network_Similarities_How_Bibliographic_Coupling_Networks_Citation_Networks_Cocitation_Networks_Topical_Networks_Coauthorship_Networks_and_Coword_Networks_Relate_to_Each_Other","249366116_Bibliographic_coupling","235276596_Jones_KS_A_Statistical_Interpretation_of_Term_Specificity_and_its_Application_in_Retrieval_Journal_of_Documentation_281_11-21","227911476_Comparison_of_the_Results_of_Bibliographic_Coupling_and_Analytic_Subject_Indexing","227798507_Bibliograpic_Coupling_Between_Scientific_Papers","227